 <item> <title>Texas To Receive More Than $1 Billion In Additional Recovery Funds</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/texas-receive-more-1-billion-additional-recovery-funds</link>
 <description>U. S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan today announced that an additional $1,072,589,804 is now available for Texas under the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act (ARRA) of 2009.  To date, Texas has received $7,439,690,398 through the ARRA. The state recently reported that recovery dollars have been used to provide funding for more than 28,000 education jobs from Jan.</description>
