 <item> <title>Texas to Receive Nearly $338 Million to Turn Around Its Persistently Lowest Achieving Schools</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/texas-receive-nearly-338-million-turn-around-its-persistently-lowest-achieving-schools</link>
 <description>U.S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan today announced that Texas will receive nearly $338 million to turn around its persistently lowest achieving schools through the School Improvement Grants (SIG) program. These funds are part of the $3.5 billion that will be made available to states this spring from money set aside in the 2009 budget and the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act. 
