 <item> <title>Texas to Receive $51.4 Million to Turn Around Its Persistently Lowest-Achieving Schools</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/texas-receive-514-million-turn-around-its-persistently-lowest-achieving-schools</link>
 <description>U.S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan today announced that Texas will receive $51.4 million to turn around its persistently lowest achieving schools through the School Improvement Grants (SIG) program. The funds are part of $546 million available to states for the SIG program in fiscal year 2010.  In fiscal year 2009, states received a total of $3.5 billion for the SIG program.</description>
